channel.title: Data Type Comparision :: IT From Scratch
channel.description: List and Tuple Type Conversion Input print(tuple(['cat', 'dog', 5])) print(list(('cat', 'dog', 5))) print(list('hello')) Output ('cat', 'dog', 5) ['cat', 'dog', 5] ['h', 'e', 'l', 'l', 'o'] Comparing Dictionarie and List Input spam = ['cats', 'dogs', 'moose'] bacon = ['dogs', 'moose', 'cats'] print(spam == bacon) # The order of list items matters Ouput
